LINE.Text: At the end of 2017, Poland's population amounted to 38,4 mln inhabitants
6,9 mln were children and youth aged 0-17
The lowest number of children throughout the entire period after World War II was born in 2003.
In 2017 the number of births amounted to 402 thous. It's still over 40% less than in 1983,
The biggest number of children is born in summer. The day on which children are born
the most often is Tuesday, the least often on Sunday
